80770>
80770>        Use Dd_debug.dg // This Provides access to dd debugger by pressing ctrl+d within any view. Good for debugging
Including file: Dd_debug.dg    (E:\DataFlex 19.0\Pkg\Dd_debug.dg)
80770>>>// dd_debug.dg - DDO debugger/inspector
80770>>>//
80770>>>// Copyright Data Access WorldWide 2003
80770>>>// John Tuohy
80770>>>//
80770>>>// By adding this to any Windows view or application (with a "use DD_Debug.dg") you can
80770>>>// inspect your DDOs and make sure they are doing what you think. To invoke this panel you
80770>>>// need to press ctrl/d (or send DebugDDs).
80770>>>//
80770>>>// As of 9.1, this also tests for sending reentrant messages to the DDO when the DDO is busy.
80770>>>// Normally, these messages are ignored - now you get an error message (so you can fix it).
80770>>>// Also, you can set a limit for number of filtered records so you can see if you are using
80770>>>// optimized and non-optimized indexes the way you think you are.
80770>>>//
80770>>>// NOTE: This package should NEVER appear in a deployed application. It is just for your
80770>>>//       own development and testing.
80770>>>
80770>>>
80770>>>
80770>>>Validate_Packages 18 0 1
80770>>>
80770>>>Define CR_LF for (Character(13)+Character(10))
80770>>>
80770>>>// This provides support for DDO Rentancy checking and for testing for
80770>>>// non-optimal finding.
80770>>>Use DD_OperationChecker.pkg
Including file: dd_OperationChecker.pkg    (E:\DataFlex 19.0\Pkg\dd_OperationChecker.pkg)
80770>>>>>// dd_OperationChecker.pkg for VDF10.0
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>// Copyright Data Access WorldWide 2003
80770>>>>>// John Tuohy
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>// One of the harder DDO errors to see is the issue of reentrancy. A number of the DDO operations are not
80770>>>>>// reentrant. When a message such as Request_Save, Request_find or Clear is sent to a DDO all DDOs are considered
80770>>>>>// to be "busy" until the operationis complete. While DDOs are busy you can not send messages to ANY other DDO in
80770>>>>>// ANY other part of your application. The file structure of DDOs and the the C structure of DDOs do not allow this.
80770>>>>>// If you do send a reentrant message while the DDOs are busy the reentrant message is ignored. Here lies the problem.
80770>>>>>// You are trying to perform some kind of DDO customization and some of these customized behaviors are ignored without
80770>>>>>// any kind of warning or error.
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>// The following DDO messages are non re-entrant. While any of these methods are being processed you cannot send any of these
80770>>>>>// messages to any DDOs.
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>//     Clear
80770>>>>>//     Clear_All
80770>>>>>//     Request_save
80770>>>>>//     Request_delete
80770>>>>>//     Request_assign
80770>>>>>//     Request_find
80770>>>>>//     Request_Superfind
80770>>>>>//     Find_by_recnum
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>// This package provides diagnostic code that checks these messages and makes sure that are not trying to call them in a busy state.
80770>>>>>// Instead of the busy operation being ignored, an error will be reported. Once you see the error, you can fix it.
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>// In addition, there is a check built in here for non-optimal finding operations. You can set the value of giNonOptimalFindCount
80770>>>>>// to a non zero value and when a find operation filters that many recods, you will get an error.
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>// IMPORTANT: This is a debug package and should never be used in deployed applications. It should be used by the developer
80770>>>>>// to test their application. Once tested, the code should be removed.
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>// To Use
80770>>>>>// ------
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>// This is used as part of DD_Debug.dg. While this could be used stand-alone you really don't want to do this.
80770>>>>>//
80770>>>>>// NOTE: This can only be used with VDF9.1 or above. If you try to use this with older packages this will not compile!
80770>>>>>
80770>>>>>Validate_Packages 9 1 0
80770>>>>>Use Data_set.pkg
80770>>>>>
80770>>>>>// This variable determines of the rentrancy tests should be performed. dd_debug will use and set this
80770>>>>>Global_variable Integer gbTestRentrancy
80770>>>>>Move 1 to gbTestRentrancy
80771>>>>>
80771>>>>>// This determines how many failed finds is considered to be non-optimal. When 0, there is no check.
80771>>>>>Global_variable Integer giNonOptimalFindCount
80771>>>>>Move 0 to giNonOptimalFindCount
80772>>>>>
80772>>>>>Procedure CheckRentrancy for DataSet handle hoDD string sMessage
80774>>>>>    String sMess sVal
80774>>>>>    
80774>>>>>    If (gbTestRentrancy=0 or operation_mode=mode_waiting) Procedure_Return
80777>>>>>    
80777>>>>>    If (OPERATION_MODE=MODE_VALIDATING and Lowercase(sMessage)<>"request_save") Begin
80779>>>>>        // mode_validating is not really a non-reentrant DD function from the runtime's point of view. The DDs
80779>>>>>        // keep track of this mode. Therefore, we will let a re-entrant DD message pass through for all cases, except
80779>>>>>        // request_save because trying to perform a save while inside of a validate is most likely wrong.
80779>>>>>        Procedure_Return
80780>>>>>    End
80780>>>>>>
80780>>>>>    
80780>>>>>    Move ("DDO re-entrant operation attempted.\n\n"+;          "Message = " - sMessage - ".  Object =" - name(hoDD) -".\n"+ ;          "\nCurrent Operation_mode is " + string(operation_mode) +;          "\nCurrent Operation_origin is " + string(operation_origin) * name(operation_origin) ) to sMess
80781>>>>>    Error DFERR_PROGRAM sMess
80782>>>>>>
80782>>>>>end_procedure
80783>>>>>
80783>>>>>Procedure NonOptimalTest for DataSet  Handle hoDD string sMessage integer iOldDif integer iFile integer iIndex
80785>>>>>    string sMess
80785>>>>>    Integer iNewDif
80785>>>>>
80785>>>>>    Move (constrain_tests_count - Constrain_found_count) to iNewDif
80786>>>>>    If (iNewDif-iOldDif>giNonOptimalFindCount) Begin
80788>>>>>        Move ("Constrained Find may not be Optimized.\n\n"+;              "Message =" - sMessage - ".  Object = " - name(hoDD) -".\n"+ ;              "Test finds exceeds the limit of" * string(giNonOptimalFindCount) * "filtered records.\n" +;              "Number of records searched = " + string(iNewDif-iOldDif) + ".") to sMess
80789>>>>>        If (iFile>0) Begin
80791>>>>>            // if iFile is zero we don't don't which file is being found (i.e. Locate_next)
80791>>>>>            Move (sMess + "\nFile = " + string(iFile) + ". Index = "+ string(iIndex) + ".") to sMess
80792>>>>>        End
80792>>>>>>
80792>>>>>        Error DFERR_PROGRAM sMess
80793>>>>>>
80793>>>>>    end
80793>>>>>>
80793>>>>>end_procedure
80794>>>>>
80794>>>>>
80794>>>>>Procedure Clear for DataSet
80796>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "clear"
80797>>>>>    forward send clear
80799>>>>>end_procedure
80800>>>>>
80800>>>>>Procedure Clear_All for DataSet
80802>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "clear_all"
80803>>>>>    forward send clear_all
80805>>>>>end_procedure
80806>>>>>
80806>>>>>Procedure Request_Save for DataSet
80808>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "request_save"
80809>>>>>    forward send request_save
80811>>>>>end_procedure
80812>>>>>
80812>>>>>Procedure Request_Delete for DataSet
80814>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "request_delete"
80815>>>>>    forward send request_delete
80817>>>>>end_procedure
80818>>>>>
80818>>>>>Procedure Request_Assign for DataSet integer iFile
80820>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "request_assign"
80821>>>>>    If (num_arguments=0) ;        forward send request_assign
80825>>>>>    else ;        forward send request_assign iFile
80828>>>>>end_procedure
80829>>>>>
80829>>>>>Procedure Find_By_Recnum for DataSet integer iFile integer iRecord
80831>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "Find_by_recnum"
80832>>>>>    forward send Find_by_recnum iFile iRecord
80834>>>>>end_procedure
80835>>>>>
80835>>>>>Procedure Request_Find for DataSet integer iMode integer iFile integer iIndex
80837>>>>>    Integer iOldDif
80837>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "request_find"
80838>>>>>    Move (constrain_tests_count - Constrain_found_count) to iOldDif
80839>>>>>    forward send request_find iMode iFile iIndex
80841>>>>>    If (giNonOptimalFindCount>0) Begin
80843>>>>>        Send NonOptimalTest self "request_find" iOldDif iFile iIndex
80844>>>>>    End
80844>>>>>>
80844>>>>>end_procedure
80845>>>>>
80845>>>>>Procedure Request_Read for DataSet integer iMode integer iFile integer iIndex
80847>>>>>    Integer iOldDif
80847>>>>>    Move (constrain_tests_count - Constrain_found_count) to iOldDif
80848>>>>>    forward send request_Read iMode iFile iIndex
80850>>>>>    If (giNonOptimalFindCount>0) Begin
80852>>>>>        Send NonOptimalTest  self "request_read" iOldDif iFile iIndex
80853>>>>>    End
80853>>>>>>
80853>>>>>end_procedure
80854>>>>>
80854>>>>>
80854>>>>>Procedure Request_Superfind for DataSet integer iMode integer iFile integer iField
80856>>>>>    Integer iOldDif
80856>>>>>    Send CheckRentrancy self "request_Superfind"
80857>>>>>    Move (constrain_tests_count - Constrain_found_count) to iOldDif
80858>>>>>    forward send Request_Superfind iMode iFile iField
80860>>>>>    If (giNonOptimalFindCount>0) Begin
80862>>>>>        Send NonOptimalTest  self "request_Superfind" iOldDif 0 0 // we don't have a file or an index
80863>>>>>    End
80863>>>>>>
80863>>>>>end_procedure
80864>>>>>
