82111>>>
82111>>>// This provides a quick and simple way to create an about package for a program.
82111>>>// You need to create a message inside you client area called Activate_About.
82111>>>// Within this message you should send the message DoAbout passing needed
82111>>>// string information.
82111>>>//
82111>>>//       Procedure Activate_About
82111>>>//           Send DoAbout sTitle sVersion sCopyright sAuthor sBitmap
82111>>>//       End_Procedure
82111>>>//    where: sTitle =     Name of application. If none provided, uses caption
82111>>>//                        bar title
82111>>>//           sVersion   = Version Line. If none provided, will be blank
82111>>>//           sCopyRight = Copyright Line. If none provided, will be blank
82111>>>//           sAuthor    = Author name, blank if none provided
82111>>>//           sBitMap    = Bitmap logo. If none provided, standard VDF bitmap
82111>>>//                        is used.
82111>>>// It is expected that you will place this in your own object package. For
82111>>>// example an order about package may look like this:
82111>>>//
82111>>>//   // OrderAbout.pkg
82111>>>//   Use StdAbout.pkg
82111>>>//   Procedure Activate_About
82111>>>//      String sTitle sCopyright sVersion sAuthor
82111>>>//      Move "My Order Entry System" to sTitle
82111>>>//      Move "Version 2.1" to sVersion
82111>>>//      Move "Copyright 1997, Super Software Inc." to sCopyright
82111>>>//      Move "John Smith"  to sAuthor
82111>>>//      Send DoAbout sTitle sVersion sCopyright sAuthor ""
82111>>>//   end_procedure
82111>>>//   // end of file.
82111>>>
82111>>>Use DfAbout.pkg
Including file: DfAbout.pkg    (C:\Projects\DF18\DbUpdateFramework\AppSrc\DfAbout.pkg)
