82839>>>>>>>>>>>
82839>>>>>>>>>>>// Help System Package
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>// Public Properties that should be set:
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property String  Help_Filename   (Help_File_Default(self))
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_General 0
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Index   0
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Keys    0
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Files   0
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//     Property Integer Help_Id_Errors  0
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>// Public messsages which are sent to this object:
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_KeyWord_Help integer Obj
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_ID_Help      integer Obj
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Context_Help         integer Obj
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Help_for_help        integer Obj
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_help_index           integer Obj
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Keys_Help            integer Obj
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_File_Help            integer Obj
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Error_Help           integer Obj
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    procedure View_Help_on_Topic        integer Obj
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>// Protected Messages:
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//        These messages invoke the Window's help system and are not
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//        directly sent by outside objects. They are sent by public
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//        "view_xxx" messages and might be used if you are creating
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//        a sub-class of an object-class.
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_System_Context_Help  integer Context_id
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_System_Help          string  Keyword
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    Procedure Exec_Context_Help         string  Context
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    Functions for converting DF help IDs to windows Help Ids
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//        Any of these can return either a string or an integer.
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_Context_id Integer ID Returns String
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert a DF help context id into a windows id. By default,
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           just return the same value (a one to one match). This is called
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           by View_Context_id_help and View_Context_Help
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_File_Id Integer File# Integer Field# Returns String
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert file and field into a help id. By default it returns the
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           file#. Called by View_File_Help.
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//    Function System_Help_Error_id Integer Id Returns String
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           Convert an error message into an ID. Right now it returns the
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           the general error context id property, Help_id_errors. This
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           will invoke general error help. If you want error support at the
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           error# level you will have to determine the program to help
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           interface yourself. Errors have a very large range and it is
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           therefore hard to come up with an automatic numbering scheme.
82839>>>>>>>>>>>//           Called by View_Error_Help.
82839>>>>>>>>>>>
82839>>>>>>>>>>>
82839>>>>>>>>>>>Use Windows.pkg
82839>>>>>>>>>>>Use WinHlp.pkg // low level help call to windows API provides global message gDoWinHelp
82839>>>>>>>>>>>Use HelpSystemConstants.pkg // constants used by help system
82839>>>>>>>>>>>
82839>>>>>>>>>>>Register_Function phoWorkspace Returns Handle
82839>>>>>>>>>>>Register_function peHelpType  returns integer
82839>>>>>>>>>>>
82839>>>>>>>>>>>class HelpSystem is an cObject
82840>>>>>>>>>>>
82840>>>>>>>>>>>    register_function Help_File_Default returns string
82840>>>>>>>>>>>
82840>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure Construct_Object
82842>>>>>>>>>>>       Forward send Construct_Object
82844>>>>>>>>>>>
82844>>>>>>>>>>>       // Help file name only. If set, this overrides all other settings.
82844>>>>>>>>>>>       Property String psHelpFile
82845>>>>>>>>>>>
82845>>>>>>>>>>>       // Help_FileName
82845>>>>>>>>>>>       //   full path name of Help file. The default value grabs its value
82845>>>>>>>>>>>       //   from .ini or environment settings. See functiob Help_file_Default
82845>>>>>>>>>>>       //
82845>>>>>>>>>>>       Property String  Private.Help_Filename (Help_File_Default(self))
82846>>>>>>>>>>>
82846>>>>>>>>>>>       // The following properties are the default values for the help files
82846>>>>>>>>>>>       // IDs for the various subjects. Setting these requires an agreement
82846>>>>>>>>>>>       // between the DF help system and the help file.
82846>>>>>>>>>>>       //
82846>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_General  0
82847>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Index    0
82848>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Keys     0
82849>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Files    0
82850>>>>>>>>>>>       Property Integer Help_Id_Errors   0
82851>>>>>>>>>>>
82851>>>>>>>>>>>       // this is now the default help object
82851>>>>>>>>>>>       Move self to Help_Object_id
82852>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
82853>>>>>>>>>>>
82853>>>>>>>>>>>   // New rules for VDF8:
82853>>>>>>>>>>>   // 1. If psHelpFile exists, find the file in the file path and use it
82853>>>>>>>>>>>   // 2. If application object exists and help type is windows, use psHelpFile from there, find in file path and use it.
82853>>>>>>>>>>>   // 3. If no help file exists, use thge old private help name (which gets the full name from the registry -only if no app object)
82853>>>>>>>>>>>   //    Last method is deprecated and only used for old applications
82853>>>>>>>>>>>   //
82853>>>>>>>>>>>   Function Help_filename returns string
82855>>>>>>>>>>>        string sHelpName
82855>>>>>>>>>>>        // If ghoWorkSpace Get Help_FileName of ghoWorkSpace to sHelpName // removed for VDF8
82855>>>>>>>>>>>
82855>>>>>>>>>>>        // If an Application object is used, take the name from there.
82855>>>>>>>>>>>        Get psHelpFile to sHelpName
82856>>>>>>>>>>>        If (sHelpName="" AND ghoApplication AND peHelpType(ghoApplication)=htWinHelp) Begin
82858>>>>>>>>>>>            Get psHelpFile of ghoApplication To sHelpName
82859>>>>>>>>>>>            //Move (psHelpPath(phoWorkspace(ghoApplication)) -"\" -sHelpName) To sHelpName
82859>>>>>>>>>>>        End
82859>>>>>>>>>>>>
82859>>>>>>>>>>>        If (sHelpName<>"") begin
82861>>>>>>>>>>>            Get_File_Path sHelpName To sHelpName
82862>>>>>>>>>>>            Function_Return sHelpName
82863>>>>>>>>>>>        end
82863>>>>>>>>>>>>
82863>>>>>>>>>>>        // if not set anywhere (and ideally it is) we use this.
82863>>>>>>>>>>>        Get Private.Help_FileName to sHelpName
82864>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return sHelpName
82865>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
82866>>>>>>>>>>>
82866>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure Set Help_FileName string sName
82868>>>>>>>>>>>        Set Private.Help_FileName to sName
82869>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
82870>>>>>>>>>>>
82870>>>>>>>>>>>
82870>>>>>>>>>>>
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    // Consider this message PRIVATE in that it should only be changed
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    // by a sub-class and not an object. It is called in construct_object
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    // before it knows about object augmentations!!!!
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    //  Sets the Help_file_name by looking at the .INI file for:
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    //        HELP_DIR    - help directory (will check environment variable
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      windir if not found - avoid this usage). If not
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      blank append "\" as required.
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    //        HELP_FILE   - help file name. If blank uses the default help
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    //                      file name
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82870>>>>>>>>>>>    Function Help_File_Default Returns String
82872>>>>>>>>>>>       String HelpFileDir HelpFileName sSubKey
82872>>>>>>>>>>>       // if using the application object we expect the help name to be
82872>>>>>>>>>>>       // defined in the application object or directly in the help object. No Exceptions
82872>>>>>>>>>>>       If (ghoApplication) function_return ""
82875>>>>>>>>>>>
82875>>>>>>>>>>>       // else if no application (and hence no WS) use an old deprecated method of checking
82875>>>>>>>>>>>       // for the module name in local_machine.
82875>>>>>>>>>>>       Get Module_name of Desktop to sSubKey
82876>>>>>>>>>>>       Get_Profile_String sSubKey HELP_DIR to HelpFileDir
82879>>>>>>>>>>>       Get_Profile_String sSubKey HELP_FILE to HelpFileName
82882>>>>>>>>>>>       // if dir exists, sure it has a "\" at the end. If no directory the
82882>>>>>>>>>>>       // dir must be blank so current directory is searched
82882>>>>>>>>>>>       If ( (HelpFileDir<>'') AND (Right(HelpFileDir,1)<>"\") ) ;          Move (HelpFileDir - '\') to HelpFileDir
82885>>>>>>>>>>>       If HelpFileName eq '' Move DEFAULT_HELP_FILENAME to HelpFileName
82888>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return (HelpFileDir - HelpFileName)
82889>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
82890>>>>>>>>>>>
82890>>>>>>>>>>>    // The System_Help_xxxx messages convert a DF help integer ID into
82890>>>>>>>>>>>    // a context value that can be used by the windows help system. If
82890>>>>>>>>>>>    // you return a number or a string. Numbers will get used for context ID
82890>>>>>>>>>>>    // help, non-numbers get used for keyword context help
82890>>>>>>>>>>>
82890>>>>>>>>>>>    // By default return ID passed. This creates a direct mapping between
82890>>>>>>>>>>>    // context IDs in your object and the context IDs in windows help.
82890>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82890>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_Context_id Integer ID Returns String
82892>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return ID
82893>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_Context_id
82894>>>>>>>>>>>
82894>>>>>>>>>>>    // Returns the file# which assumes that we have a direct mapping between
82894>>>>>>>>>>>    // the file number and a window's help context_id. We are ignoring field#
82894>>>>>>>>>>>    // in this case (although your augmentation would not have to). If the
82894>>>>>>>>>>>    // file# is 0, return a the HELP_ID context id.
82894>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82894>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_File_Id Integer File# Integer Field# Returns String
82896>>>>>>>>>>>       String rVal
82896>>>>>>>>>>>       if File# eq 0 Move (Help_id_files(self)) to rVal
82899>>>>>>>>>>>       Else Move File# to rVal
82901>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return Rval
82902>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_File_id
82903>>>>>>>>>>>
82903>>>>>>>>>>>    // Convert an error id into a help context id. Return the general
82903>>>>>>>>>>>    // Help id property value. We do this because error number have
82903>>>>>>>>>>>    // a rather large range (1-9000) and just using the number would consume
82903>>>>>>>>>>>    // too much of the context id space.
82903>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82903>>>>>>>>>>>    Function System_Help_Error_id Integer Id Returns String
82905>>>>>>>>>>>       Function_Return (Help_Id_Errors(self))
82906>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function // System_Help_Error_id
82907>>>>>>>>>>>
82907>>>>>>>>>>>    // Use this if you want your help context to be keyword based
82907>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82907>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure View_Context_KeyWord_Help integer Obj
82909>>>>>>>>>>>       String Context
82909>>>>>>>>>>>       If Obj gt 0 ;          Get Help_Context of obj HELP_CONTEXT_KEYWORD to Context
82912>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_System_Help Context
82913>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
82914>>>>>>>>>>>
82914>>>>>>>>>>>    // Use this if you want your help context to be ID based
82914>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82914>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure View_Context_ID_Help integer Obj
82916>>>>>>>>>>>       Integer Context_ID
82916>>>>>>>>>>>       String Context
82916>>>>>>>>>>>       If Obj gt 0 ;          Get Help_Context of Obj HELP_CONTEXT_ID to Context_ID
82919>>>>>>>>>>>       Get System_Help_Context_id Context_Id to Context
82920>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_Context_Help Context
82921>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
82922>>>>>>>>>>>
82922>>>>>>>>>>>    // Use this is you want the object requesting help to support either
82922>>>>>>>>>>>    // keyword or context ID help (it will use whatever it finds first).
82922>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82922>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure View_Context_Help integer Obj
82924>>>>>>>>>>>       String Context
82924>>>>>>>>>>>       If Obj gt 0 ;          Get Help_Context of obj HELP_CONTEXT_ID_OR_KEY to Context
82927>>>>>>>>>>>       if (left(context,1)) in '0123456789' ;          Get System_Help_Context_id Context to Context
82930>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_Context_Help Context
82931>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
82932>>>>>>>>>>>
82932>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure View_Help_for_Help Integer obj
82934>>>>>>>>>>>        Send Exec_System_Help HELP_FOR_HELP_STRING
82935>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
82936>>>>>>>>>>>
82936>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure View_Help_Index integer obj
82938>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_Context_Help (Help_id_index(self))
82939>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure // View_help_index
82940>>>>>>>>>>>
82940>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure View_Keys_Help Integer Obj
82942>>>>>>>>>>>        Send Exec_Context_Help (Help_id_keys(self))
82943>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
82944>>>>>>>>>>>
82944>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure View_File_Help Integer Obj
82946>>>>>>>>>>>       String Context FilFld
82946>>>>>>>>>>>       Integer File# Field# Dot
82946>>>>>>>>>>>       If Obj gt 0 Begin
82948>>>>>>>>>>>          // This should return the file and field as a string in
82948>>>>>>>>>>>          // FFF.fff format (F=File, f=format).
82948>>>>>>>>>>>          Get Help_Context of Obj HELP_CONTEXT_DATAFILE to FilFld
82949>>>>>>>>>>>          // Parse FilFld into File# and Field#.
82949>>>>>>>>>>>          Pos '.' in FilFld to Dot
82951>>>>>>>>>>>>
82951>>>>>>>>>>>          if Dot ne 0 begin
82953>>>>>>>>>>>             Left FilFld to File#  (dot-1)
82955>>>>>>>>>>>>
82955>>>>>>>>>>>             Mid  FilFld to Field# 255 (dot+1)
82958>>>>>>>>>>>>
82958>>>>>>>>>>>          End
82958>>>>>>>>>>>>
82958>>>>>>>>>>>       End
82958>>>>>>>>>>>>
82958>>>>>>>>>>>       Get System_Help_File_id File# Field# to Context
82959>>>>>>>>>>>       Send Exec_Context_Help Context
82960>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure // View_File_Help
82961>>>>>>>>>>>
82961>>>>>>>>>>>    //  View help on an error. Current version uses context id help.
82961>>>>>>>>>>>    //  The error number should be in global integer last_err
82961>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82961>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure View_Error_Help Integer Obj
82963>>>>>>>>>>>        String Context
82963>>>>>>>>>>>        If Obj gt 0 ;           Get Help_Context of obj HELP_CONTEXT_ERROR to Context
82966>>>>>>>>>>>        if (left(context,1)) in '0123456789' ;           Get System_Help_Error_id Context to Context
82969>>>>>>>>>>>        Send Exec_Context_Help Context
82970>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
82971>>>>>>>>>>>
82971>>>>>>>>>>>    // View list of help topics.
82971>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82971>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure View_Help_on_Topic Integer obj
82973>>>>>>>>>>>        Send Exec_System_Help HELP_ON_TOPIC_STRING
82974>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
82975>>>>>>>>>>>
82975>>>>>>>>>>>    // Request context help. If context is a number assume that it is
82975>>>>>>>>>>>    // context id help, else assume it is keyword help.
82975>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82975>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure Exec_Context_Help string Context
82977>>>>>>>>>>>       if (left(context,1)) in '0123456789' ;    // if first character is a          Send Exec_System_Context_Help Context  // numeric we assume ID help
82980>>>>>>>>>>>       else ;                                    // otherwise we assume key-          Send Exec_System_Help Context          // word help.
82982>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure // Exec_Context_Help
82983>>>>>>>>>>>
82983>>>>>>>>>>>    // NOTE: the following two messages are the only messages that directly make calls
82983>>>>>>>>>>>    //       to the windows API. This is important. These two messages could be changed
82983>>>>>>>>>>>    //       to call other help systems (e.g. HTML help) and the rest of the high level
82983>>>>>>>>>>>    //       program remains the same. These are the only two messages that are
82983>>>>>>>>>>>    //       expected to be windows help centric.
82983>>>>>>>>>>>
82983>>>>>>>>>>>    // Get Context Id help for passed ID. Use help file as defined
82983>>>>>>>>>>>    // in Help_filename. If id is 0 use general help id (which must be
82983>>>>>>>>>>>    // defined.
82983>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82983>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure Exec_System_Context_Help integer Context_id
82985>>>>>>>>>>>        If Context_Id eq 0 ; // if zero, see if we have a contents page            Move (Help_Id_General(self)) to Context_id
82988>>>>>>>>>>>        If Context_Id eq 0 ; // if still zero, jump to the topics popup dialog            Send Exec_System_Help HELP_ON_TOPIC_STRING
82991>>>>>>>>>>>        Else ;            Send gDoWinHelp WH_INTCONTEXT (Help_Filename(self)) Context_Id
82993>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
82994>>>>>>>>>>>
82994>>>>>>>>>>>    // Get keyword help for passed keyword. Use help file as defined
82994>>>>>>>>>>>    // in help_filename.
82994>>>>>>>>>>>    //
82994>>>>>>>>>>>    procedure Exec_System_Help string Keyword
82996>>>>>>>>>>>        If Keyword eq HELP_FOR_HELP_STRING ;            Send gDoWinHelp WH_HELPONHELP
82999>>>>>>>>>>>        else if (Keyword eq HELP_ON_TOPIC_STRING OR KeyWord="");            Send gDoWinHelp WH_FINDER (Help_Filename(self))
83003>>>>>>>>>>>        else ;            Send gDoWinHelp WH_STRINGCONTEXT (Help_Filename(self)) KeyWord
83005>>>>>>>>>>>    end_procedure
83006>>>>>>>>>>>
83006>>>>>>>>>>>end_class
