83018>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83018>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_SET_MODE
83018>>>>>>>/// @Description Allows switching between set-oriented and record oriented fetch modes.
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// If DF_FILE_SET_MODE is set to True, the driver will fetch a set of records
83018>>>>>>>/// for each find. If DF_FILE_SET_MODE is False, the driver will fetch only one
83018>>>>>>>/// record at a time. This attribute can also be specified in the .INT file during
83018>>>>>>>/// migration through Flex2SQL. This settings is normally used alongside
83018>>>>>>>/// DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS to set the number of rows to return and DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE
83018>>>>>>>/// to turn on local caching.
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// Note: Turning off set-mode can have a detrimental impact on performance. Unless
83018>>>>>>>/// there is a specific reason to do otherwise, this option should be left on.
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// Default value: True
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83018>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83018>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83018>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
83018>>>>>>>/// @See DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE
83018>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT OPTIMIZE {FOR_SET | ONE_ROW}
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83018>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83018>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83018>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Mode for the FileNumber. True for set-mode, False for one-row mode.
83018>>>>>>>/// @Example
83018>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
83018>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of Orderhea.File_Number to True
83018>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_SET_MODE of Orderhea.File_Number to boolVar
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_SET_MODE                             For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+5)
83018>>>>>>>
83018>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83018>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_DATABASENAME
83018>>>>>>>/// @Description Returns a string containing the name of the database where the
83018>>>>>>>/// table referenced by the passed File Number resides. This is a READ ONLY
83018>>>>>>>/// attribute. Note that because Oracle doesn't support the concept of multiple
83018>>>>>>>/// databases on one server, this attribute is not valid for Oracle.
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83018>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83018>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex, MySQLFlex, PGFlex
83018>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
83018>>>>>>>/// @See
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_DATABASENAME of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83018>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83018>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Name of the Database
83018>>>>>>>/// @Example
83018>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
83018>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_DATABASENAME of Orderhea.File_Number to strVal
83018>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_DATABASENAME                         For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+6)
83018>>>>>>>
83018>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83018>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS
83018>>>>>>>/// @Description Controls the maximum number of rows retrieved by a Find GT/LT
83018>>>>>>>/// operation. The driver will automatically retrieve and cache this many rows
83018>>>>>>>/// for future find GT/LT operations. Setting this property to a very high
83018>>>>>>>/// value can be inefficient from a UI perspective but may be advisable for
83018>>>>>>>/// local processing of rows (such as in a batch process).
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// Default value: 10
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83018>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83018>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83018>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-15 by Oliver Nelson
83018>>>>>>>/// @See DF_FILE_SET_MODE DF_FILE_CACHE_MODE
83018>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT MAX_ROWS_TO_QUERY {integer}
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_DATABASENAME of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83018>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83018>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Attribute Value
83018>>>>>>>/// @Example
83018>>>>>>>/// Open Orderhea
83018>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS of Orderhea.File_Number to 10
83018>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS of Orderhea.File_Number to intVal
83018>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_MAX_ROWS                             For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+7)
83018>>>>>>>
