83018>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM
83018>>>>>>>/// @Description When creating records on a table with RECNUM support, the
83018>>>>>>>/// record number is returned after creation. When this attribute is false, the newly
83018>>>>>>>/// created record's RECNUM is not returned from the server. This could result in a
83018>>>>>>>/// slight performance improvement when many records are being created in a loop.
83018>>>>>>>/// The optimization, however, is negligible.  Having this attribute set to false can
83018>>>>>>>/// have detrimental effects if used improperly; i.e. DD-based saves or UI-based
83018>>>>>>>/// operations. Thus, this should almost always be set to true unless there is a
83018>>>>>>>/// compelling reason to do otherwise.
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// Default Value: True
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83018>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83018>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83018>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-31 by Aaron Gulack
83018>>>>>>>/// @See
83018>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83018>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83018>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83018>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Boolean variable. false to not retrieve record number, true otherwise.
83018>>>>>>>
83018>>>>>>>/// @Example
83018>>>>>>>/// open ORDERHEA
83018>>>>>>>/// Handle  hFile
83018>>>>>>>/// Boolean bRetrieve
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// Set_Attribute DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM of hFile to false
83018>>>>>>>/// Get_Attribute DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM of hFile To bRetrieve
83018>>>>>>>Define DF_FILE_RETRIEVE_RECNUM                      For (DF_FILE_RECORD_REREAD+17)
83018>>>>>>>
83018>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83018>>>>>>>/// @Name        DF_FILE_NAME_SPACE
83018>>>>>>>/// @Description In Postgres, schemas are objects where all the tables,views and indexes
83018>>>>>>>/// are stored. Separate schemas are used to specify relational data. This attribute is
83018>>>>>>>/// used to set the name of the schema where a table is created. Schema's do not account
83018>>>>>>>/// for any physical space but are merely used as theory to explain the order of a database.
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83018>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
83018>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     PGFlex
83018>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-07-25 by Aaron Gulack
83018>>>>>>>/// @See
83018>>>>>>>/// @INTOPT
83018>>>>>>>///
83018>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Get_Attribute DF_FILE_NAME_SPACE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83018>>>>>>>/// @Syntax Set_Attribute DF_FILE_NAME_SPACE of {FileNumber} to {variable}
83018>>>>>>>/// @Param  FileNumber            Number of the file
83018>>>>>>>/// @Param  variable              Name of the Schema
83018>>>>>>>/// @Example
83018>>>>>>>/// open ORDERHEA
