83020>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83020>>>>>>>//Comment Block Template
83020>>>>>>>//======================
83020>>>>>>>
83020>>>>>>>/// @Name {Name of the command for indexing} (used for documentation)
83020>>>>>>>/// @Description {Short Command Description} (used for documentation)
83020>>>>>>>///     The description can be multiple lines, and contain HTML tags.
83020>>>>>>>///     The other tokens will have HTML encoded so we can show stuff
83020>>>>>>>///     like <param1> properly. A blank line will automatically be
83020>>>>>>>///         translated into a paragraph break in the documentation, so
83020>>>>>>>///     no need for <br> or <p> tags.
83020>>>>>>>///
83020>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions {Assumptions made in order for the command to work}
83020>>>>>>>/// @Status {Obsolete, Internal, or Public} (used for documentation)
83020>>>>>>>/// @Drivers {DB2Flex, MySQLFlex, ORAFlex, PgFlex, SQLFlex or All} (used for documentation)
83020>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote {Date and author of the last revision}
83020>>>>>>>/// @See {list of related commands}
83020>>>>>>>///
83020>>>>>>>/// @Syntax {Syntax of use} (used for documentation)
83020>>>>>>>/// @Param {Each parameter with a brief description} (used for documentation)
83020>>>>>>>/// @DBMS {List of supported databases}
83020>>>>>>>/// @DataFlex {List of supported DataFlex versions}
83020>>>>>>>/// @Usage {Different uses command can have multiple syntaxes} (used for documentation)
83020>>>>>>>///
83020>>>>>>>/// @Example {An example of the command being used} (used for documentation)
83020>>>>>>>
83020>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83020>>>>>>>/// @Name        DO_GETFILENUMBER_DRIVERNAME
83020>>>>>>>/// @Description Retrieves the current driver name and or the file number
83020>>>>>>>/// that will be used by the macro commands.
83020>>>>>>>///
83020>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83020>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal Use Only
83020>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
83020>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2009-07-14 By Ian Smith
83020>>>>>>>/// @See
83020>>>>>>>
83020>>>>>>>//Most commands use DO_GETFILENUMBER_DRIVERNAME so this code was being duplicated
83020>>>>>>>//all the time. It has been moved to this method to remove that duplication.
83020>>>>>>>Procedure MertechInc_Get_Driver_name Global
83022>>>>>>>    //If we have a file number get its driver, else find first loaded Mertech driver
83022>>>>>>>    If MertechInc_FileNumber GT 0 ;        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_DRIVER of MertechInc_FileNumber to MertechInc_DriverName
83027>>>>>>>    Else Begin
83028>>>>>>>        If (MertechInc_CurrentDriver > "") Move MertechInc_CurrentDriver to MertechInc_DriverName
83031>>>>>>>        Else Begin
83032>>>>>>>            Get_Attribute DF_NUMBER_DRIVERS to MertechInc_iCount
83035>>>>>>>            For MertechInc_iLoop from 1 to MertechInc_iCount
83041>>>>>>>>
83041>>>>>>>                Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_NAME of MertechInc_iLoop to MertechInc_DriverName
83044>>>>>>>                Move (UPPERCASE(MertechInc_DriverName)) to MertechInc_DriverName
83045>>>>>>>                If (MertechInc_DriverName EQ ORAFLEX  or MertechInc_DriverName EQ SQLFLEX or MertechInc_DriverName EQ MDSDB2 or ;                    MertechInc_DriverName EQ MDSPgSQL or MertechInc_DriverName EQ MDSMySQL) Move MertechInc_iCount to MertechInc_iLoop
83048>>>>>>>                Else Move "" to MertechInc_DriverName
83050>>>>>>>            Loop
83051>>>>>>>>
83051>>>>>>>        End
83051>>>>>>>>
83051>>>>>>>    End
83051>>>>>>>>
83051>>>>>>>
83051>>>>>>>    //Ensure that we return a valid Mertech driver.
83051>>>>>>>    If (MertechInc_DriverName NE ORAFLEX  and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE SQLFLEX  and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE MDSDB2   and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE MDSPgSQL and ;        MertechInc_DriverName NE MDSMySQL     ) ;        Begin
83053>>>>>>>
83053>>>>>>>        //Report invalid driver
83053>>>>>>>//        Error 25100 ("Invalid Driver - file" * String(MertechInc_FileNumber))
83053>>>>>>>//        Error 25100 ("Mertech.inc - Not a Mertech driver (file number " * String(MertechInc_FileNumber) * ")")
83053>>>>>>>        Error 25100 ("Mertech.inc - Not a Mertech driver. File" * String(MertechInc_FileNumber) * "Driver" * Trim(MertechInc_DriverName) )
83054>>>>>>>>
83054>>>>>>>
83054>>>>>>>        //Set MertechInc_FileNumber to MertechInc_Invalid_Driver so that the commands can
83054>>>>>>>        //determine if the driver is valid. MertechInc_FileNumber is use instead of
83054>>>>>>>        //MertechInc_DriverName as integer conparisons are quicker than string conparisons
83054>>>>>>>        Move MertechInc_Invalid_Driver to MertechInc_FileNumber
83055>>>>>>>    End
83055>>>>>>>>
83055>>>>>>>End_Procedure
83056>>>>>>>
83056>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83056>>>>>>>/// @Name        MertechInc_Pre_Size_String
83056>>>>>>>/// @Description Returns a string full of spaces.
83056>>>>>>>///
83056>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
83056>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal
83056>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     n/a
83056>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2009-12-02 By Gandalf Hernandez
83056>>>>>>>/// @See
83056>>>>>>>Function MertechInc_Pre_Size_String Global Integer iSize Returns String
83058>>>>>>>   Local String sWork
83058>>>>>>>   Local Integer iBlocks iRemainder
83058>>>>>>>
83058>>>>>>>   If (iSize <= 1) Begin
83060>>>>>>>      // marcelo 06/28/2000 implemented logic to avoid VDF 7 crashing problems
83060>>>>>>>          If FMAC_VERSION eq 7 Move 1000 to iSize
83063>>>>>>>          Else Move 16384 to iSize
83065>>>>>>>   End
83065>>>>>>>>
83065>>>>>>>
83065>>>>>>>   // Build the string in blocks of 32, to speed things up
83065>>>>>>>   // If the string is less than 32 bytes, just fill it up regularly
83065>>>>>>>   Move (iSize / 32) to iBlocks
83066>>>>>>>   Move (Mod(iSize, 32)) to iRemainder
83067>>>>>>>
83067>>>>>>>   If (iBlocks > 0) Begin
83069>>>>>>>      Move (Repeat("                                ", iBlocks)) to sWork
83070>>>>>>>      Move (Append (sWork, (Repeat(" ", iRemainder)))) to sWork
83071>>>>>>>   End
83071>>>>>>>>
83071>>>>>>>   Else Move (Repeat(" ", iSize)) to sWork
83073>>>>>>>
83073>>>>>>>   Function_Return sWork
83074>>>>>>>End_Function
83075>>>>>>>
83075>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
83075>>>>>>>/// @Name        MertechInc_Set_DecSep
83075>>>>>>>/// @Description Saves the current decimal separator and sets the decimal
83075>>>>>>>/// separator to '.'.
