84049>>>>>>>/// @Name        SET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
84049>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to set the number of milliseconds
84049>>>>>>>/// an SQL statement waits for a database lock to be released before timing
84049>>>>>>>/// out. Locks are used with transactions to maintain atomicity. If a lock is
84049>>>>>>>/// not released before the timeout, then the statement will fail and an error
84049>>>>>>>/// will be raised. By default, the timeout is set to -1, indicating that
84049>>>>>>>/// statements will wait indefinitely before timing out.
84049>>>>>>>///
84049>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84049>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84049>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex
84049>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-07 by Aaron Gulack
84049>>>>>>>/// @See                 GET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
84049>>>>>>>///
84049>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SET_SQL_LOCAL_TIMEOUT of {server} to {variable}
84049>>>>>>>/// @Param server                       Name of the server
84049>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Number of milliseconds to wait until timeout
84049>>>>>>>///
84049>>>>>>>/// @Example
84049>>>>>>>/// SET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT of "localhost" to 6000
84049>>>>>>>
84049>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84049>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
84049>>>>>>>/// @Description This command returns the number of milliseconds an SQL
84049>>>>>>>/// statement will wait for a database lock to be released. If the lock
84049>>>>>>>/// is not released before the timeout, then the statement will fail and
84049>>>>>>>/// an error will be raised. Note that the default value is -1, indicating
84049>>>>>>>/// that the statement will wait indefinitely.
84049>>>>>>>///
84049>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84049>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84049>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex
84049>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-07 by Aaron Gulack
84049>>>>>>>/// @See                 SET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT
84049>>>>>>>///
84049>>>>>>>/// @Syntax GET_SQL_LOCAL_TIMEOUT of {server} to {variable}
84049>>>>>>>/// @Param server                       Name of the server
84049>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Variable to hold the number of milliseconds
84049>>>>>>>///
84049>>>>>>>/// @Example
84049>>>>>>>/// GET_SQL_LOCK_TIMEOUT of "localhost" to iTimeout
84049>>>>>>>
84049>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
