84067>>>>>>>/// @Name        CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE
84067>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to call a stored procedure on the SQL
84067>>>>>>>/// backend. To successfully call a procedure with this command, a string
84067>>>>>>>/// must be passed containing a valid procedure name. In addition, if the
84067>>>>>>>/// procedure takes any arguments, they must also be passed using the constant
84067>>>>>>>/// "passing" along with all of the needed arguments. If the procedure has a
84067>>>>>>>/// return value, then SQL_GET_FUNCTION_RETURN or SQL_FETCH_NEXT_ROW can be
84067>>>>>>>/// used to get the value(s). If an error is found then the indicator "Err"
84067>>>>>>>/// is set to true.
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84067>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84067>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
84067>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-09-25 by Aaron Gulack
84067>>>>>>>/// @See
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Syntax CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE {procedure} Passing {variable}
84067>>>>>>>/// @Param procedure            Full name of the procedure
84067>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Argument being passed (can be multiple)
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Example
84067>>>>>>>/// CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE "sys.sp_addmessage" passing 50003 15 "Please enter a valid date"
84067>>>>>>>
84067>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84067>>>>>>>/// @Name        CALL_SQLSERVER_PROCEDURE
84067>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to call a stored procedure on the SQL
84067>>>>>>>/// backend. To successfully call a procedure with this command, a string
84067>>>>>>>/// must be passed containing a valid procedure name. In addition, if the
84067>>>>>>>/// procedure takes any arguments, they must also be passed using the constant
84067>>>>>>>/// "passing" along with all of the needed arguments. If the procedure has a
84067>>>>>>>/// return value, then SQL_GET_FUNCTION_RETURN, SQL_FETCH_NEXT_ROW or
84067>>>>>>>/// GET_PROCEDURE_RETURN can be used to get the value(s). If an error is found
84067>>>>>>>/// then the indicator "Err" is set to true.
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Status      Deprecated
84067>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex
84067>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 by Aaron Gulack
84067>>>>>>>/// @See                 CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Syntax CALL_SQLSERVER_PROCEDURE {procedure} Passing {variable}
84067>>>>>>>/// @Param procedure            Full name of the procedure
84067>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Argument to be passed (can be multiple)
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Example
84067>>>>>>>/// CALL_SQLSERVER_PROCEDURE "sys.sp_addmessage" passing 50003 15 "Please enter a valid date"
84067>>>>>>>
84067>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84067>>>>>>>/// @Name        END_CALL_PROCEDURE
84067>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to close any open cursors created
84067>>>>>>>/// by the respective stored procedure. Cursors are used in MSSQL to make
84067>>>>>>>/// the results from one procedure temporarily available to other procedures
84067>>>>>>>/// or triggers. To avoid causing unwanted results, it is good practice to
84067>>>>>>>/// use this command once a procedure call is completed.
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84067>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84067>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex
84067>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 by Aaron Gulack
84067>>>>>>>/// @See                 CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Syntax END_CALL_PROCEDURE
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Example
84067>>>>>>>/// CALL_STORED_PROCEDURE "sys.sp_spaceused" Passing "Customer"
84067>>>>>>>/// GET_PROCEDURE_RETURN to sValue
84067>>>>>>>/// END_CALL_PROCEDURE
84067>>>>>>>/// Showln sValue
84067>>>>>>>
84067>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84067>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_PROCEDURE_RETURN
84067>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to get a returned value from a stored
84067>>>>>>>/// procedure using MSSQL. Note that this command can only handle one
84067>>>>>>>/// returned value and must be used after the procedure has already been
