84067>>>>>>>
84067>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84067>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_MIRROR_SERVER
84067>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to get the name of the server
84067>>>>>>>/// and database being used for failover mirroring. Mirroring must
84067>>>>>>>/// be properly set up in SQL Server for this command to return the
84067>>>>>>>/// correct values.
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84067>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84067>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     SQLFlex v9.2 and above
84067>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 by Aaron Gulack
84067>>>>>>>/// @See                 SET_MIRROR_SERVER
84067>>>>>>>///
84067>>>>>>>/// @Syntax GET_MIRROR_SERVER to {server} {database}
84067>>>>>>>/// @Param server                       Variable to hold the name of the mirrored server
84067>>>>>>>/// @Param database                     Variable to hold the name of the mirrored database
84067>>>>>>>///
