84097>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME
84097>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to find out how long until a
84097>>>>>>>/// specific temporary license for a driver expires. If 0 is returned,
84097>>>>>>>/// then the license is not a temporary license. If -1 is returned, then
84097>>>>>>>/// the license has already expired. Otherwise, the number returned
84097>>>>>>>/// is the number of days until the license will expire.
84097>>>>>>>///
84097>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84097>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84097>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
84097>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 Aaron Gulack
84097>>>>>>>/// @See                 GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING
84097>>>>>>>///
84097>>>>>>>/// @Syntax GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME to {variable}
84097>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Variable to hold the days until expiration
84097>>>>>>>///
84097>>>>>>>/// @Example
84097>>>>>>>/// GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME to iExpire
84097>>>>>>>/// Showln iExpire
84097>>>>>>>
84097>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84097>>>>>>>/// @Name        SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING
84097>>>>>>>/// @Description This command is used to set a custom warning message to
84097>>>>>>>/// be displayed when a temporary license for a driver is close to expiring.
84097>>>>>>>/// Note that since the license evaluation is done during Login and before
84097>>>>>>>/// any open calls, this command should be called before either of those.
84097>>>>>>>///
84097>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84097>>>>>>>/// @Status      Public
84097>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
84097>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-02 by Aaron Gulack
84097>>>>>>>/// @See                 GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME
84097>>>>>>>///
84097>>>>>>>/// @Syntax SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING to {variable}
84097>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     New warning message for expiring license
84097>>>>>>>///
84097>>>>>>>/// @Example
84097>>>>>>>/// SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING to "Your license is about to expire."
84097>>>>>>>/// Login "localhost" "" "" "sql_drv"
84097>>>>>>>
84097>>>>>>>//=============================================================================
84097>>>>>>>/// @Name        GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH
84097>>>>>>>/// @Description This command will return the current path of the license
84097>>>>>>>/// associated with the driver.
84097>>>>>>>///
84097>>>>>>>/// @Assumptions
84097>>>>>>>/// @Status      Internal
84097>>>>>>>/// @Drivers     All
84097>>>>>>>/// @VersionNote Last Revised: 2013-10-01 by Aaron Gulack
84097>>>>>>>/// @See                 SET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_WARNING GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_EXPIRATION_TIME
84097>>>>>>>///
84097>>>>>>>/// @Syntax GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH to {variable}
84097>>>>>>>/// @Param variable                     Variable to hold the path of the license
84097>>>>>>>
84097>>>>>>>Function MertechInc_GET_DRIVER_LICENSE_PATH Global Returns String
84099>>>>>>>    Local String sReturnValue
84099>>>>>>>
84099>>>>>>>    DO_GETFILENUMBER_DRIVERNAME 0
84101>>>>>>>    If (MertechInc_FileNumber <> -1) Begin
84103>>>>>>>        Get MertechInc_Pre_Size_String 4096 to sReturnValue
84104>>>>>>>        Call_Driver 0 MertechInc_DriverName Function CALLDRV_LICENSE_ENVIRONMENT_SET CALLBACK 0 PASSING sReturnValue MertechInc_Blank CALLDRV_LICENSE_PATH RESULT MertechInc_iRet
84109>>>>>>>        If MertechInc_iRet EQ -1 INDICATE ERR True
84112>>>>>>>    End
84112>>>>>>>>
84112>>>>>>>
84112>>>>>>>    Function_Return sReturnValue
84113>>>>>>>End_Function
