85514>>>>>Use StatusPanel.pkg
Including file: StatusPanel.pkg    (C:\Projects\DF18\DbUpdateFramework\AppSrc\StatusPanel.pkg)
85514>>>>>>>// StatPnl.pkg - creates the standard status_panel object.
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// This is the default Status Panel object used by any of the Visual DataFlex classes that
85514>>>>>>>// invoke the standard status panel. The standard has always been that the package name
85514>>>>>>>// is StatPnl.pkg and the name of the object is Status_Panel. As of 12.0, there are major
85514>>>>>>>// changes in the way the status panel operates The Sentinel based external status panel used in
85514>>>>>>>// prior revisions has been replace with status panel that is part of the application.
85514>>>>>>>// This should work much better and faster than the old sentinel based solution.
85514>>>>>>>// While the way this operates has changed, the interface has not and therefore this should work
85514>>>>>>>// with most applications.
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// As of 12.0, we have added a global handle that contains the object ID of this status panel.
85514>>>>>>>// This variable ghoStatusPanel can be used in place of the object name Status_Panel. This provides
85514>>>>>>>// a cleaner more robust interface.
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// Compatibility Note:
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// When used in the standard way, this change will require no changes. A developer will only need to
85514>>>>>>>// change their code if they've modified the sentinel program, which was a difficult thing to do.
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// If for some reason you application will not work using this as a replacement for the old status
85514>>>>>>>// panel, you've probably done something special with the old status-panel. If you don't want to
85514>>>>>>>// figure out how to use the new one and you want to continue using the old one you are going to need
85514>>>>>>>// to add some code to include the old status panel in your application. Add the following to your project (your src).
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// Use StatPnl.pkg    // Make sure you load the new status panel object first. this is not optional!
85514>>>>>>>// Use OldStatPnl.pkg // load the old status panel. Status_Panel is now this old object
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// If you do this, you will lose access to the new status-panel via Status_Panel. However, you
85514>>>>>>>// can still access the new object via the ghoStatusPanel handle.
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// Creating your own Status Panel objects
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// If a developer wishes to create a custom panel, they should use this package as their template.
85514>>>>>>>// This panel can be visually modeled and changed any way you wish. Just save your new custom panel
85514>>>>>>>// with a different file and object name and direct your status panel request to the new object.
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// If the new panel changes the interface and updates objects that are not currently defined, you
85514>>>>>>>// want to make sure you send the message ProcessEvents after you've updated the object. This allows
85514>>>>>>>// the object to paint when inside of a tight loop. For example, if you wanted to add a progress
85514>>>>>>>// bar (cProgressBar) you would want to Send ProcessEvents after you update the progress bar.
85514>>>>>>>// e.g.
85514>>>>>>>//       Procedure UpdateStatusBar
85514>>>>>>>//           Send DoAdvance of oProgressBar
85514>>>>>>>//           Send ProcessEvents
85514>>>>>>>//       End_Procedure
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// of course, if you use the standard interfaces in status bar and your forward send these
85514>>>>>>>// messages this will be done for you.
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// the standard Interface for status panels are:
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// Send Initialize_StatusPanel - initializes values for caption, title & message
85514>>>>>>>// Send Start_StatusPanel      - start the status panel
85514>>>>>>>// Send Stop_StatusPanel       - stop the status panel
85514>>>>>>>// Send Update_StatusPanel     - update the status panel's action area
85514>>>>>>>// Get  Check_StatusPanel      - check for cancel (if cancel or pbCancel is set, close the panel)
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// Get/Set Caption_Text - updates the caption bar
85514>>>>>>>// Get/Set Title_Text   - updates the title area
85514>>>>>>>// Get/Set Message_Text - updates the Message area
85514>>>>>>>// Get/Set Action_Text  - updates the action area
85514>>>>>>>// Get/Set Button_Text  - updates the button area
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// Get/Set Allow_cancel_state - determines if panel can be canceled
85514>>>>>>>// Send EnableCancelButton - code you should provide to enable/disable cancel button
85514>>>>>>>//
85514>>>>>>>// ghoStatusPanel - global handle that points to the standard status panel.
85514>>>>>>>Use cProcessStatusPanel.pkg
85514>>>>>>>Use cCJSkinFramework.pkg
85514>>>>>>>//Use cAnimation.pkg
