85837>>>>>>>
85837>>>>>>>// SQL Back-ends (iSQLDbType in the tSQLKeywords struct).
85837>>>>>>>// They can have slightly different SQL keywords. 
85837>>>>>>>// Note: If a new type is added to the list,
85837>>>>>>>//       the struct array xxx must be adjusted
85837>>>>>>>//       so that it is filled with all SQL
85837>>>>>>>//       keywords for that new type.
85837>>>>>>>Enum_List
85837>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeMSSQL
85837>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeMySQL
85837>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeOracle
85837>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeDB2 
85837>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypePostgre 
85837>>>>>>>    Define EN_DbTypeDataFlex // Embedded database.
85837>>>>>>>End_Enum_List 
85837>>>>>>>
85837>>>>>>>// We need to have our "own" constants for the standard DataFlex data types.
85837>>>>>>>// These can be used with SQL functions such as e.g. SQLColumnAdd, instead
85837>>>>>>>// of using one of the driver specific integer constants such as e.g. "SQL_VARCHAR".
85837>>>>>>>// We need to re-define the standard constants because several driver constants
85837>>>>>>>// have the same value and we need to be able to distinguish which data type to use when
85837>>>>>>>// e.g. creating a column with embedded SQL (ESQL).
85837>>>>>>>Enum_List 
85837>>>>>>>    Define DF_ASCII_DUF     for 1500
85837>>>>>>>    Define DF_BCD_DUF       for 1499
85837>>>>>>>    Define DF_BINARY_DUF    for 1494
85837>>>>>>>    Define DF_DATE_DUF      for 1498
85837>>>>>>>    Define DF_DATETIME_DUF  for 1493
85837>>>>>>>    Define DF_TEXT_DUF      for 1495
85837>>>>>>>End_Enum_List
85837>>>>>>>
85837>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeMSSQL       for "Microsoft SQL Server"
85837>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeMySQL       for "MySQL"
85837>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeOracle      for "Oracle"
85837>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeDB2         for "IBM DB2"
85837>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypePostgre     for "PostgreSQL"
85837>>>>>>>Define CS_DbTypeDataFlex    for "DataFlex Embedded"
85837>>>>>>>
85837>>>>>>>    Define SQL_TEXT for (DF_TEXT + 1024)
85837>>>>>>>
85837>>>>>>>Define SQL_CHARBIT          for (DF_BINARY + 1024)
85837>>>>>>>Define SQL_LONGVARCHARBIT   for (DF_BINARY + 1025)
85837>>>>>>>Define SQL_VARCHARBIT       for (DF_BINARY + 1026)
85837>>>>>>>
