Including file: Base64Functions.pkg    (C:\Projects\DF18\DbUpdateFramework\AppSrc\Base64Functions.pkg)
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//> This package enables base64 encoding and decoding of strings:
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//>
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//>     Get EncodeString of oBase64Functions sValue to sValue
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//>     Get DecodeString of oBase64Functions sValue to sValue
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//>
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//> Remember to set the "max argument size" if dealing with very large
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//> strings.
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//>
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//> For 17.1 and later the functionality of this package is based on two functions (Base64Encode and
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//> Base64Decode) that are built into the runtime.
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//>
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//> But for versions up to and including 17.0 it's based on the vdfBase64.dll file that was obtained
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//> from DAE that have kindly allowed me to distribute it to other DF developers. Programs including
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//> this package will give off an error on start-up if vdfBase64.dll is not found in the /bin folder
86028>>>>>>>>>>>//> if the VDF runtime. You will find the DLL in the /programs folder of the StureApsPublicLib workspace
86028>>>>>>>>>>>
86028>>>>>>>>>>>Use VdfBase.pkg
86028>>>>>>>>>>>
86028>>>>>>>>>>>// Functions in vdfBase64.dll
86028>>>>>>>>>>>External_Function xxBase64Encode "vdfbase64Encode" vdfBase64.dll Pointer pBuffer Returns Integer
86029>>>>>>>>>>>External_Function xxBase64Decode "vdfbase64Decode" vdfBase64.dll Pointer pBuffer Returns Integer
86030>>>>>>>>>>>External_Function xxBase64Free   "vdfbase64Free"   vdfBase64.dll Pointer pBuffer Returns Integer
86031>>>>>>>>>>>
86031>>>>>>>>>>>// Structure
86031>>>>>>>>>>>Struct txxfBase64Buffer
86031>>>>>>>>>>>    Pointer pData
86031>>>>>>>>>>>    Integer iLength
86031>>>>>>>>>>>End_Struct 
86031>>>>>>>>>>>
86031>>>>>>>>>>>Global_Variable Integer oBase64Functions
86031>>>>>>>>>>>
86031>>>>>>>>>>>Object _oBase64Functions is a cObject
86033>>>>>>>>>>>    Move Self to oBase64Functions
86034>>>>>>>>>>>
86034>>>>>>>>>>>
86034>>>>>>>>>>>    Function EncodeString String sValue Returns String
86037>>>>>>>>>>>        Address pBase64
86037>>>>>>>>>>>        String sResult
86037>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iVoid
86037>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (Base64Encode(AddressOf(sValue), Length(sValue))) to pBase64
86038>>>>>>>>>>>        Move pBase64 to sResult
86039>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (Free(pBase64)) to iVoid
86040>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return sResult
86041>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
86042>>>>>>>>>>>
86042>>>>>>>>>>>    Function DecodeString String sValue Returns String
86045>>>>>>>>>>>        Address pBinary
86045>>>>>>>>>>>        String sBinary
86045>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iVoid iLen
86045>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (Base64Decode(AddressOf(sValue), &iLen)) to pBinary
86046>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (Repeat(Character(0), iLen)) to sBinary
86047>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (MemCopy(AddressOf(sBinary), pBinary, iLen)) to iVoid
86048>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (Free(pBinary)) to iVoid
86049>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return sBinary
86050>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
86051>>>>>>>>>>>
86051>>>>>>>>>>>End_Object
