86052>>>>>>>>>>>// *** Windows 32bit file handling wrapper class ***
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//
86052>>>>>>>>>>>
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 05-09-2000 **WvA: Changed namingconvention of all classes and methods to new standard
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   This may be painfull for some of you, but it was really needed as it was
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   getting messy. The "vs" -prefix we used before was confusing and could
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   unintentionally have been interpreted as "Vdf-GUIdance String".
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// The used naming-convention is:
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//     - a prefix of "vWin32_" for every external function declaration
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//     - a prefix of the letter "v" for the full API name for the vdf-wrapper function.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// By using this we are guarding ourselves for conflicts with variable declarations
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// of DataAccess in the future.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// Or at least almost as the letter "v" is now also synonym for variant (duh~!)
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// mm-dd-yyyy Author Description
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   vSHGetFolderPath added to retrieve the new shell folders
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   vGetWindowsDirectory
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   vGetTempFileName
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   vGetTempPath
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 11-17-2001 **WvA: Removed User Interface Error popups such as Error handling.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   This is an absolute need for WebApp. We expect you to handle the
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   error in your application anyways. Changed this for:
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   vDeleteFile, vCopyFile, vMoveFile and vRenameFile
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 03-02-2002 **WvA: vRemoveDirectory added
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 03-11-2002 **WvA: The parameter lpdword in the external function declaration for
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   vWin32_SHBrowsForFolder can cause compiler errors.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   It is renamed too avoid this.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 11-11-2002 **WvA: Codecleanup, vcSelectFile_Dialog is now cvSelectFile_Dialog, its
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   function vSelectedFileName is now just SelectedFileName
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   Removed the local keyword in the variable declarations
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 10-17-2003 **WvA: Cleaned up function vSelect_File and added code to destroy the dynamically
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   created file-open dialog
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 02-12-2004 **WvA: Allan Ankerstjeme pointed me into a bug for the vCreateTempFileInPath
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   in that it didn't exactly return the correct filename of the file created.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   This has now been taken care of.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 02-19-2004 **WvA: Removed all API declarations from the package itself to improve readability
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   These declarations are now included from the vWin32fh header file.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 02-19-2004 **WvA: Changed the default way in which the standard file handling works
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   Before today one could always undo the operation, as of now you cannot as
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   the default was a silly one using unnecessary resources (mainly diskspace)
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   Since i don't really expect someone to use that feature it has been removed.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   One can however restore to the old way of handling by simply calling the
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   vWin32fhCompatibilityMode procedure ONE time before accessing any of the
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   filehandling operations
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 02-19-2004 **WvA: The functions ParseFolderName, ParseFileName and ParseFileExtenstion added
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   as well as the StringFromRightOfChar function.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 02-19-2004 **WvA: sfoFormatDisk function added which can use to format a floppydisk
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   DISABLED now as testing shows that it does not work as advertised...
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 02-20-2004 **WvA: The function vDDE_Error_Handler didn't pass the errornumber on to the DDE_Error_To_String function
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   Moved the hardcoded strings from vDDE_Error_Handler to define declarations for easier translation later on.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 09-10-2004 **WvA: Added the ToAnsi function to the fileoperations method so that
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   extended characters are treated ok too.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   Reported by Flemming from
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 12-17-2004 **WvA: Changed vFilePathExists to be global, reported by Peter van Mil
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 12-28-2004 **WvA: WebApp compatibility added by introducing compiler directives
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 03-10-2006 **WvA: Added more CSIDL types to our header file for use with the vSHGetFolderPath function
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 01-02-2007 **WvA: Set NoChangeDir_State on vSelect_File and vSelectSaveFile to True but changed it back due to side effects.
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   Added vSelectSavefile function to create a file save dialog
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   Fixed ParseFolderName which was horribly broken (thanks for the reports)
86052>>>>>>>>>>>//                   Added vParentPath function to retrieve the parent "node" of a path
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 01-04-2008 **WvA: Fixed vCreateTempFileInPath as the function wasn't working
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 10-04-2009 **WvA: Added vshCreateDirectoryEx from Micheal Mullan, moved filedialogs to cvFileDialogs.pkg
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 01-11-2010 **WvA: Added vWin32_APIFilesize as supplied by Renato Villa, to get the filesize of the specified file. See http://support.dataaccess.com/forums/showthread.php?t=41982
86052>>>>>>>>>>>// 10-02-2011 **WvA: Added vCSIDL_SYSTEMX86, courtesy of Ola Eldoy for pointing this out and providing the define statement.
