86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Courtesy Of Vincent Oorsprong
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>// This function formats the time in a picture-string passed
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Picture      Meaning
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    h         Hours with no leading zero for single-digit hours; 12-hour clock
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    hh        Hours with leading zero for single-digit hours; 12-hour clock
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    H         Hours with no leading zero for single-digit hours; 24-hour clock
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    HH        Hours with leading zero for single-digit hours; 24-hour clock
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    m         Minutes with no leading zero for single-digit minutes
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    mm        Minutes with leading zero for single-digit minutes
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    s         Seconds with no leading zero for single-digit seconds
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    ss        Seconds with leading zero for single-digit seconds
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    t         One character time marker string, such as A or P
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    tt        Multicharacter time marker string, such as AM or PM
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>// For example, to get the time string  "11:29:40 PM"
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    use the following picture string: "hh" : "mm" : "ss tt"
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86129>>>>>>>>>>>>>External_function vWin32_GetTimeFormat "GetTimeFormatA" Kernel32.Dll ;  Dword LCID Dword dwFlags Pointer lpsSystemTime Pointer lpFormat Pointer lpTimeStr ;  Integer cchTime Returns Integer
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Courtesy Of Vincent Oorsprong
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>// This function formats the date in a picture-string passed
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>// Picture      Meaning
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    d         Day of month as digits with no leading zero for single-digit days.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    dd        Day of month as digits with leading zero for single-digit days.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    ddd       Day of week as a three-letter abbreviation. The function uses the
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              LOCALE_SABBREVOAYMAME value associated with the specified locale.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    dddd      Day of week as its full name. The function uses the LOCALE_SDAYNAME
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              value associated with the specified locale.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    M         Month as digits with no leading zero for single-digit months.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    MM        Month as digits with leading zero for single-digit months.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    MMM       Month as a three-letter abbreviation. The function uses the
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              LOCALE_SABBREVMONTHNAME value associated with the specified locale.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    MMMM      Month as its full name. The function uses the LOCALE_SMONTHNAME value
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              associated with the specified locale.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    y         Year as last two digits, but with no leading zero for years less than 10.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    yy        Year as last two digits, but with leading zero for years less than 10.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    yyyy      Year represented hy full four digits.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    gg        Period/era string. The function uses the CAL_SERASTRING value associated
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              with the specified locale. This element is ignored if the date to be formatted
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>//              does not have an associated era or period string.
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>// For example, to get the date string  "Wed, Aug 31 94"
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>// use the following picture string:    "ddd","MMM dd yy"
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86130>>>>>>>>>>>>>External_function vWin32_GetDateFormat "GetDateFormatA" Kernel32.Dll ;  Dword LCID Dword dwFlags Pointer lpsSystemTime Pointer lpFormat Pointer lpDateStr ;  Integer cchDate Returns Integer
86131>>>>>>>>>>>>>
