86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>// SHCreateDirectoryEx
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    Note  This function is available through Microsoft Windows XP Service Pack 2 (SP2) and Windows Server 2003.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    It might be altered or unavailable in subsequent versions of Windows.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    This function creates a file system folder whose fully qualified path is given by pszPath. If one or more
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    of the intermediate folders do not exist, they are created as well. SHCreateDirectoryEx also verifies that
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//    the files are visible. If they are not visible, expect one of the following:
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//        * If hwnd is set to a valid window handle, a message box is displayed warning the user that he or she
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//        might not be able to access the files. If the user chooses not to proceed, the function returns
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//        ERROR_CANCELLED.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//        * If hwnd is set to NULL, no user interface is displayed and the function returns ERROR_CANCELLED.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//        Returns ERROR_SUCCESS if successful. If the operation fails, other error codes can be returned,
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//        including those listed here. For values not specifically listed, see System Error Codes.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//      161  ERROR_BAD_PATHNAME                The pszPath parameter was set to a relative path.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//      206  ERROR_FILENAME_EXCED_RANGE     The path pointed to by pszPath is too long.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//      3    ERROR_PATH_NOT_FOUND            The system cannot find the path pointed to by pszPath. The path may contain an invalid entry.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//      80   ERROR_FILE_EXISTS                The directory exists.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//      183  ERROR_ALREADY_EXISTS            The directory exists.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//      1223 ERROR_CANCELLED                The user canceled the operation.
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//        int SHCreateDirectoryEx(
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//            HWND hwnd,
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//            LPCTSTR pszPath,
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//            const SECURITY_ATTRIBUTES *psa
86133>>>>>>>>>>>>>//        );
