87621>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87621>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Procedure SQLBindFile Integer iFileNum
87623>>>>>>>>>>>>>        tColumnMap tColumnMap
87623>>>>>>>>>>>>>        tColumnMap tColumnMap
87623>>>>>>>>>>>>>        String[] sBindFileColumns
87624>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer[] iBufferColumn
87625>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iColCnt i iDateFormat iResultColumnType iBindFileColumnType
87625>>>>>>>>>>>>>        String sColumnName
87625>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Variant vFieldValue
87625>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Boolean isRecnumTable
87625>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87625>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
87639>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87639>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87639>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_RECNUM_TABLE of iFileNum to isRecnumTable
87642>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Get ptColumnMap to tColumnMap
87643>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87643>>>>>>>>>>>>>        If (tColumnMap.iFileNum <> iFileNum) Begin
87645>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Move iFileNum to tColumnMap.iFileNum
87646>>>>>>>>>>>>>            
87646>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // First we build an array of the column names (in order) from the file buffer to bind to
87646>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Get_Attribute DF_FILE_NUMBER_FIELDS of iFileNum to iColCnt
87649>>>>>>>>>>>>>            For i from 0 to iColCnt
87655>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87655>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (isRecnumTable) Get_Attribute DF_FIELD_NAME of iFileNum i to sColumnName
87660>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Else Move "" to sColumnName
87662>>>>>>>>>>>>>                
87662>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Move (Uppercase(sColumnName)) to sBindFileColumns[i]
87663>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Loop
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // Next we iterate over the columns in the resultset.  Any column names that match we 
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // set its match location into an array that maps each resultset column to its matching
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // column number in the file buffer.  If there is no match, we set that resultset
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // column mappped column to -1.
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            //
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // Since Arrays are zero based and columns are numbered from 1, when we actually map
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // to set the value, we need to add 1 to array indexer to get the proper resultset
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // column AND we need to add 1 to the mapped-to column since it was loaded into a zero
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // based array also.  (Ex: vResultColumn[0] = 2 means column 1 from the resultset maps
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            // to Column 3 of the file buffer)
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            
87664>>>>>>>>>>>>>            SQL_GET_NUM_COLS to iColCnt
87674>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87674>>>>>>>>>>>>>            For i from 1 to iColCnt
87680>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87680>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_NAME i to sColumnName
87696>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87696>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // Because SearchArray returns -1 if there isn't a match, we don't need to do
87696>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // anything to make an "unmapped column" have a value of -1.
87696>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Move (SearchArray(Uppercase(sColumnName), sBindFileColumns)) to tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i-1]
87697>>>>>>>>>>>>>                
87697>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // If the types don't match between the columns, then "unmap" the column.  This
87697>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // should only occur when you're not mapping to the same file as the resultset.
87697>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // In this case, sql.pkg silently does nothing, so we need to duplicate this instead
87697>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // of generating an error.  If the mapping is to a string, then any type can be
87697>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // converted to a string so its okay.
87697>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i-1] <> -1) Begin
87699>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of i DFTYPE to iResultColumnType
87716>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87716>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    Get_Attribute DF_FIELD_TYPE of iFileNum (tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i-1]) to iBindFileColumnType
87719>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    
87719>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    // If the conversion is to string (even if the resultset column is something
87719>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    // else) its ok, so Break out of the If block before we muck things up.
87719>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iBindFileColumnType = DF_ASCII) Break
87722>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87722>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    // Otherwise, break the mapping
87722>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iResultColumnType <> iBindFileColumnType) Move -1 to tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i-1]
87725>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End
87725>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87725>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Loop
87726>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87726>>>>>>>>>>>>>            
87726>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Set ptColumnMap to tColumnMap
87727>>>>>>>>>>>>>        End
87727>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87727>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87727>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Get SQL_USE_DATAFLEX_DATEFORMAT to iDateFormat
87728>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Set SQL_USE_DATAFLEX_DATEFORMAT to True
87729>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Clear iFileNum
87730>>>>>>>>>>>>>        For i from 0 to (SizeOfArray(tColumnMap.vResultColumn)-1)
87736>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87736>>>>>>>>>>>>>            If (tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i] > -1) Begin
87738>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_FETCH_COLUMN (i+1) into vFieldValue
87743>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Set_Field_Value iFileNum (tColumnMap.vResultColumn[i]) to vFieldValue
87746>>>>>>>>>>>>>            End
87746>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87746>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Loop
87747>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87747>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Set_Attribute DF_FILE_STATUS of iFileNum to DF_FILE_ACTIVE
87750>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Set SQL_USE_DATAFLEX_DATEFORMAT to iDateFormat
87751>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
87752>>>>>>>>>>>>>    
87752>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Function SQLGetData Integer iCol Integer iLen Returns String
87754>>>>>>>>>>>>>        String data
87754>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer retlen
87754>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87754>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
87768>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87768>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87768>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CHUNK_SIZE to iLen
87785>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87785>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_GET_DATA_CHUNK COLUMN iCol OFFSET (piDataChunkOffset(Self)) to data retlen
87795>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87795>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Set piDataChunkOffset to (piDataChunkOffset(Self)+retlen)
87796>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87796>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return data
87797>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
87798>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87798>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Function SQLColumnMap String sColname Returns Integer
87800>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iNumColumns i iIndex
87800>>>>>>>>>>>>>        String[] cols
87801>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87801>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
87815>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87815>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87815>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Get SQLStmtAttribute SQLSTMTATTRIB_COLUMNCOUNT to iNumColumns
87816>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87816>>>>>>>>>>>>>        For i from 1 to iNumColumns
87822>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87822>>>>>>>>>>>>>            SQL_GET_COL_NAME i to cols[i-1]
87838>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87838>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Move (trim(Uppercase(cols[i-1]))) to cols[i-1]
87839>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Loop
87840>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87840>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87840>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (trim(Uppercase(sColname))) to sColname
87841>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Move (SearchArray(sColname, cols)) to iIndex
87842>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return (iIndex+1)  // even if searcharray returns -1 (not found) this expects 0 for not found, so it's ok
87843>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
87844>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87844>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Function SQLStmtAttribute Integer iAttribId Returns String
87846>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iCnt
87846>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87846>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
87860>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87860>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87860>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Case Begin
87860>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLSTMTATTRIB_COLUMNCOUNT)
87862>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_NUM_COLS to iCnt
87872>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87872>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Function_Return iCnt
87873>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
87874>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLSTMTATTRIB_ROWCOUNT)
87877>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_NUM_ROWS to iCnt
87887>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87887>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87887>>>>>>>>>>>>>                //DAC Driver doesn't know the rowcount before the first fetch.
87887>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (giSQLCompatibilityMode=SQL_DAC_HIGH_COMPATABILITY) Begin 
87889>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (pisBeforeFetch(Self)) Function_Return -1
87892>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End
87892>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87892>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87892>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Function_Return iCnt
87893>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
87894>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLSTMTATTRIB_ROWCOUNT_TYPE)
87897>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // TODO: Need something to indicate the quality of the SQL_GET_NUM_ROWS, or fake till I make it
87897>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
87898>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLSTMTATTRIB_NUMMESSAGES)
87901>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Function_Return -1
87902>>>>>>>>>>>>>                // TODO: Are the messages returned in SQLGetMessage from the driver, or from the underlying connection?
87902>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
87903>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case Else
87903>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Case End
87903>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87903>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
87904>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87904>>>>>>>>>>>>>    Function SQLColAttribute Integer iCol Integer iAttribId Returns String
87906>>>>>>>>>>>>>        String sValue
87906>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iSQLType
87906>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Integer iDFType
87906>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87906>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_SET_CURRENT_CURSOR_STMT to (piCursorNum(Self))
87920>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87920>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol SQLTYPE to iSQLType
87937>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87937>>>>>>>>>>>>>        SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol DFTYPE to iDFType
87954>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87954>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
87954>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Case Begin
87954>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_SIZE)
87956>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol SIZE to sValue
87973>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87973>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87973>>>>>>>>>>>>>                //DAC Driver uses different values. 
87973>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (giSQLCompatibilityMode=SQL_DAC_HIGH_COMPATABILITY) Begin 
87975>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iSQLType=12) Move (Integer(sValue-1)) to sValue
87978>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iDFType=5) Move "0" to sValue
87981>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iSQLType=40)  Move "10" to sValue
87984>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End 
87984>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
87984>>>>>>>>>>>>>                
87984>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
87985>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_PRECISION)
87988>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol DECIMALS to sValue
88005>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88005>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88006>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_LABEL)
88009>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol COLUMN_NAME to sValue
88026>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88026>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88027>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_BASECOLUMNNAME)
88030>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol COLUMN_NAME to sValue
88047>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88047>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88047>>>>>>>>>>>>>                //DAC Driver doesn't use Base Column Name. 
88047>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (giSQLCompatibilityMode=SQL_DAC_HIGH_COMPATABILITY) Begin 
88049>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    Move "" to sValue   
88050>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End 
88050>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88050>>>>>>>>>>>>>                
88050>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88051>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_BASETABLENAME)
88054>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol TABLE_NAME to sValue
88071>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88071>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88072>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_SQLTYPE)
88075>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Move iSQLType to sValue
88076>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88076>>>>>>>>>>>>>                //DAC Driver uses different values. 
88076>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (giSQLCompatibilityMode=SQL_DAC_HIGH_COMPATABILITY) Begin 
88078>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iSQLType=2) Move "3" to sValue
88081>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iSQLType=-99) Move "12" to sValue
88084>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iSQLType=40)  Move "91" to sValue
88087>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End 
88087>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88087>>>>>>>>>>>>>                
88087>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88088>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_NULLABLE)
88091>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol NULLABLE to sValue
88108>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88108>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88109>>>>>>>>>>>>>            Case (iAttribId = SQLCOLATTRIB_DFTYPE)
88112>>>>>>>>>>>>>                SQL_GET_COL_ATTRIBUTE of iCol DFTYPE to sValue
88129>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88129>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88129>>>>>>>>>>>>>                //DAC Driver uses different values. 
88129>>>>>>>>>>>>>                If (giSQLCompatibilityMode=SQL_DAC_HIGH_COMPATABILITY) Begin 
88131>>>>>>>>>>>>>                    If (iDFType = 5) Move "0" to sValue
88134>>>>>>>>>>>>>                End 
88134>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
88134>>>>>>>>>>>>>                Case Break
88135>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Case End
88135>>>>>>>>>>>>>        
88135>>>>>>>>>>>>>        Function_Return sValue
88136>>>>>>>>>>>>>    End_Function
88137>>>>>>>>>>>>>
