89874>>>>>>>
89874>>>>>>>// The cConnection class is the new SQL connections class for DF 19.
89874>>>>>>>// If an object of the cConnection class hasn't been instantiated we use a "dummy" class in its place.
89874>>>>>>>
89874>>>>>>>// We're making references to this object handle so we need it defined
89874>>>>>>>// here as well as for the cDbUpdateHandler class
89874>>>>>>>
89874>>>>>>>    Global_Variable Handle ghoSQLConnectionHandler
89874>>>>>>>    
89874>>>>>>>Class cSQLConnectionHandler is a cObject  
89875>>>>>>>    
89875>>>>>>>    Procedure Construct_Object
89877>>>>>>>        Forward Send Construct_Object
89879>>>>>>>        Move Self to ghoSQLConnectionHandler
89880>>>>>>>        
89880>>>>>>>        Property Handle phoSQLConnectionIniFile (Create(Self,RefClass(cSQLConnectionIniFile))) 
89881>>>>>>>        
89881>>>>>>>        // Driver default value settings:
89881>>>>>>>        // Note: When the object is created the corresponding values
89881>>>>>>>        // from the driver .int files are read.
89881>>>>>>>        // Sample: Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_NUMERIC of {driverNumber} to {StringVariable}
89881>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueASCII    ""
89882>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueBinary   ""
89883>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueDate     ""
89884>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueDateTime ""
89885>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueNumeric  ""
89886>>>>>>>        Property String psDriverDefaultValueText     ""
89887>>>>>>>        
89887>>>>>>>        // Driver "nullability" settings:
89887>>>>>>>        // Note: When the object is created the corresponding values
89887>>>>>>>        // from the driver .int files are read.
89887>>>>>>>        // Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_ASCII of {driverNumber} to {BooleanVariable}
89887>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableASCII    False
89888>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableBinary   False
89889>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableDate     False
89890>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableDateTime False
89891>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableNumeric  False
89892>>>>>>>        Property Boolean pbDriverDefaultNullableText     False
89893>>>>>>>
89893>>>>>>>        // *** This is the central point of connection data for the Database Update Framework ***
89893>>>>>>>        //     It is private because the get/set version also updates the DAW/Mertech
89893>>>>>>>        //     driver interfaces.
89893>>>>>>>        //     There are also procedure/function pairs to set/get individual data members
89893>>>>>>>        //     of the struct they are all routed throu this struct property.
89893>>>>>>>        Property tSQLConnection Private.pSQLConnection
89894>>>>>>>
89894>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
89895>>>>>>>    
89895>>>>>>>    Procedure End_Construct_Object             
89897>>>>>>>        Boolean bReadSettings 
89897>>>>>>>        tSQLConnection SQLConnection 
89897>>>>>>>        tSQLConnection SQLConnection 
89897>>>>>>>
89897>>>>>>>        Forward Send End_Construct_Object
89899>>>>>>>
89899>>>>>>>        // Now is the time to read and apply SQL connection settings.
89899>>>>>>>        Get SetupSQLConnection True to SQLConnection   
89900>>>>>>>        // ToDo: Should we use two pSQLConnection properties; one for the "from" database (in case of not Embedded);
89900>>>>>>>        //       and one for the "to" database??
89900>>>>>>>        Set Private.pSQLConnection to SQLConnection
89901>>>>>>>    End_Procedure    
89902>>>>>>>    
89902>>>>>>>    // *** Properties ***
89902>>>>>>>    // All connection related "properties" (get/set pairs) are really done by changing the
89902>>>>>>>    // private.pSQLConnection struct connection property. These "properties" are 
89902>>>>>>>    // merely here for conveniance.
89902>>>>>>>    //           
89902>>>>>>>    // The pSQLConnection get/set are here so we have a "central hub"
89902>>>>>>>    // where we update data to/from the DAW & Mertech driver interfaces and this framework.
89902>>>>>>>    // This struct property contains all the connection data.
89902>>>>>>>    //
89902>>>>>>>    Procedure Set pSQLConnection tSQLConnection SQLConnection
89904>>>>>>>        Boolean bIsDaw bIsMertech bOK
89904>>>>>>>        
89904>>>>>>>        Set Private.pSQLConnection to SQLConnection 
89905>>>>>>>        
89905>>>>>>>        // When starting a program we might not have a connection id yet:
89905>>>>>>>        If (SQLConnection.sConnectionID = "" or SQLConnection.sDriverID = DATAFLEX_ID) Begin
89907>>>>>>>            Procedure_Return
89908>>>>>>>        End                 
89908>>>>>>>>
89908>>>>>>>        
89908>>>>>>>        // After we have set the class property we need to tell the DAW/Mertech
89908>>>>>>>        // driver interfaces about the change & make a new login.
89908>>>>>>>        Get SQLLogin SQLConnection to bOK
89909>>>>>>>        If (bOK = False) Begin
89911>>>>>>>            Error DFERR_PROGRAM "Login error."       
89912>>>>>>>>
89912>>>>>>>        End 
89912>>>>>>>>
89912>>>>>>>        
89912>>>>>>>        // Now is the time to setup our driver default values by reading the driver .int file:
89912>>>>>>>        Send SetupDriverDefaults SQLConnection.sDriverID
89913>>>>>>>        
89913>>>>>>>    End_Procedure                 
89914>>>>>>>    
89914>>>>>>>    // Similar to _SqlCheckCurrentDriver but generates no error and it doesn't 
89914>>>>>>>    // attempt to load the driver.
89914>>>>>>>    // Returns true if the passed driver is SQL based.        
89914>>>>>>>    Function IsSQLDriver String sDriverID Returns Boolean
89916>>>>>>>        Boolean bOK                         
89916>>>>>>>        Integer iDriver
89916>>>>>>>        
89916>>>>>>>        Get IsDAWSQLDriver sDriverID to bOK
89917>>>>>>>
89917>>>>>>>        If (bOK = False) Begin
89919>>>>>>>            Get IsMertechDriver sDriverID to bOK
89920>>>>>>>        End                                     
89920>>>>>>>>
89920>>>>>>>
89920>>>>>>>        Function_Return bOK
89921>>>>>>>    End_Function
89922>>>>>>>            
89922>>>>>>>    // Reads the driver .int file and sets class properties of the cDbUpdateFunctionLibrary accordingly.
89922>>>>>>>    Procedure SetupDriverDefaults String sDriverID
89924>>>>>>>        String sAttributeValue                                               
89924>>>>>>>        Integer iDriverID
89924>>>>>>>        Boolean bNULL bSQLDriver
89924>>>>>>>        
89924>>>>>>>        Get IsSQLDriver sDriverID to bSQLDriver
89925>>>>>>>        If (bSQLDriver = False) Begin
89927>>>>>>>            Procedure_Return
89928>>>>>>>        End
89928>>>>>>>>
89928>>>>>>>            
89928>>>>>>>        Get DriverIndex sDriverID to iDriverID
89929>>>>>>>        
89929>>>>>>>        // Driver default values for various data types:
89929>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_ASCII of iDriverID      to sAttributeValue
89932>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueASCII                                   to sAttributeValue
89933>>>>>>>
89933>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_BINARY of iDriverID     to sAttributeValue
89936>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueBinary                                  to sAttributeValue
89937>>>>>>>
89937>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_DATE of iDriverID       to sAttributeValue
89940>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueDate                                    to sAttributeValue
89941>>>>>>>
89941>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_DATETIME of iDriverID   to sAttributeValue
89944>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueDateTime                                to sAttributeValue
89945>>>>>>>
89945>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_NUMERIC of iDriverID    to sAttributeValue
89948>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueNumeric                                 to sAttributeValue
89949>>>>>>>
89949>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_DEFAULT_TEXT of iDriverID       to sAttributeValue
89952>>>>>>>        Set psDriverDefaultValueText                                    to sAttributeValue
89953>>>>>>>        
89953>>>>>>>        // The default setting for the "nullability" of newly created ASCII columns.
89953>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_ASCII      of iDriverID to bNULL
89956>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableASCII to bNULL
89957>>>>>>>        
89957>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_BINARY     of iDriverID to bNULL
89960>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableBinary to bNULL
89961>>>>>>>        
89961>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_DATE       of iDriverID to bNULL
89964>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableDate to bNULL
89965>>>>>>>        
89965>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_DATETIME   of iDriverID to bNULL
89968>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableDateTime to bNULL
89969>>>>>>>        
89969>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_NUMERIC    of iDriverID to bNULL
89972>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableNumeric to bNULL
89973>>>>>>>        
89973>>>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_DRIVER_DEFAULT_NULLABLE_TEXT       of iDriverID to bNULL
89976>>>>>>>        Set pbDriverDefaultNullableText to bNULL
89977>>>>>>>        
89977>>>>>>>    End_Procedure
89978>>>>>>>    
89978>>>>>>>    Function SQLLogin tSQLConnection SQLConnection Returns Boolean
89980>>>>>>>        Boolean bOK bIsDaw bIsMertech bTrusted 
89980>>>>>>>        String sConnectionString sServer sDatabase sUserId sPassword sDriverID sCheck
89980>>>>>>>        Handle hoErrorObj hoDriver hoIniFile 
89980>>>>>>>        Integer iDriverID
89980>>>>>>>        
89980>>>>>>>        Move False to bOK
89981>>>>>>>        
89981>>>>>>>        Get IsDAWSQLDriver SQLConnection.sDriverID to bIsDaw
89982>>>>>>>        If (bIsDaw = False) Begin
89984>>>>>>>            Get IsMertechDriver SQLConnection.sDriverID to bIsMertech
89985>>>>>>>            If (bIsMertech = False) Begin
89987>>>>>>>                Function_Return False
89988>>>>>>>            End
89988>>>>>>>>
89988>>>>>>>        End  
89988>>>>>>>>
89988>>>>>>>        
89988>>>>>>>        Move Error_Object_Id to hoErrorObj
89989>>>>>>>        Move Self to Error_Object_Id        
89990>>>>>>>        
89990>>>>>>>        Get phoSQLConnectionIniFile to hoIniFile
89991>>>>>>>        Get ConstructConnectionString SQLConnection.sDriverID SQLConnection.sServer SQLConnection.sDatabase SQLConnection.bTrusted SQLConnection.sUserID SQLConnection.sPassword to sConnectionString
89992>>>>>>>        Get DriverIndex SQLConnection.sDriverID to iDriverID
89993>>>>>>>        If (iDriverID = 0) Begin
89995>>>>>>>            Move hoErrorObj to Error_Object_Id
89996>>>>>>>            Function_Return False
89997>>>>>>>        End
89997>>>>>>>>
89997>>>>>>>        
89997>>>>>>>        // There's a bug in Mertech drivers creating "an Exception error" in the debugger (probably will crash an application too.)
89997>>>>>>>        If (bIsMertech = False) Begin
89999>>>>>>>            Set_Attribute DF_DRIVER_SILENT_LOGIN of iDriverID to SQLConnection.bSilentLogin
90002>>>>>>>        End
90002>>>>>>>>
90002>>>>>>>        
90002>>>>>>>        Get Create (RefClass(cDbUpdateDatabaseDriver)) to hoDriver
90003>>>>>>>        Set psDriverID of hoDriver to SQLConnection.sDriverID
90004>>>>>>>        Get DbLogin    of hoDriver sConnectionString SQLConnection.sServer SQLConnection.sDatabase SQLConnection.bTrusted SQLConnection.sUserID SQLConnection.sPassword to bOK
90005>>>>>>>        Send Destroy   of hoDriver
90006>>>>>>>        Move hoErrorObj to Error_Object_Id
90007>>>>>>>        
90007>>>>>>>        Function_Return bOK
90008>>>>>>>    End_Function
90009>>>>>>>    
90009>>>>>>>    Function pSQLConnection Returns tSQLConnection
90011>>>>>>>        tSQLConnection SQLConnection
