92687>>>>>    Function SqlUtilUpdateIntFile Integer hTable Returns Boolean           
92689>>>>>        String sOrgFormat sNewFormat sRootName sDatabaseName sPhysicalFileName sDriverID sDataPath         
92689>>>>>        Boolean bOpened bOK bMertech
92689>>>>>        
92689>>>>>        Move CS_OEM_Txt  to sOrgFormat
92690>>>>>        Move CS_ANSI_Txt to sNewFormat
92691>>>>>        Get AutoConnectionIDLogin to bOK
92692>>>>>        Send Ignore_Error of Error_Object_Id DFERR_MISSING_VALUE
92693>>>>>        Open hTable //Mode DF_EXCLUSIVE
92695>>>>>        Send Trap_Error of Error_Object_Id DFERR_MISSING_VALUE
92696>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_OPENED of hTable to bOpened
92699>>>>>        
92699>>>>>        // ToDo: What to do if we cannot open the table?!
92699>>>>>        If (bOpened = False) Begin
92701>>>>>            Function_Return False
92702>>>>>        End
92702>>>>>>
92702>>>>>        
92702>>>>>        Get psDriverID to sDriverID
92703>>>>>        Get IsMertechDriver sDriverID to bMertech
92704>>>>>        If (bMertech = True) Begin       
92706>>>>>            Get psDataPathFirstPart to sDataPath
92707>>>>>            Get vFolderExists sDataPath to bOK
92708>>>>>            If (bOK = False) Begin
92710>>>>>                Error DFERR_PROGRAM "Function SqlUtilUpdateIntFile; psDataPath not found!"
92711>>>>>>
92711>>>>>                Function_Return False    
92712>>>>>            End                      
92712>>>>>>
92712>>>>>            Get vFolderFormat sDataPath to sDataPath 
92713>>>>>            Get_Attribute DF_FILE_ROOT_NAME of hTable to sRootName
92716>>>>>            Get _TableNameOnly sRootName to sDatabaseName
92717>>>>>            Move sDatabaseName to sPhysicalFileName
92718>>>>>            Move (sPhysicalFileName + ".int") to sPhysicalFileName
92719>>>>>            Get _MertechSqlUtilCreateIntFile hTable sDataPath sPhysicalFileName to bOK
92720>>>>>            Function_Return (bOK = True)
92721>>>>>        End
92721>>>>>>
92721>>>>>        
92721>>>>>        Move False to Err
92722>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_TABLE_CHARACTER_FORMAT of hTable to sOrgFormat
92725>>>>>        Move (Uppercase(sOrgFormat)) to sOrgFormat       
92726>>>>>        // Lets swap the OEM/ANSI format, just to make a change in Structure_Start below (and back),
92726>>>>>        // to "touch" the table so the driver feels there has been a change and updates the .int file.
92726>>>>>        Move (If(sOrgFormat = CS_OEM_Txt, CS_ANSI_Txt, CS_OEM_Txt)) to sNewFormat
92727>>>>>        
92727>>>>>        Structure_Start hTable
92728>>>>>            Set_Attribute DF_FILE_TABLE_CHARACTER_FORMAT of hTable to sNewFormat
92731>>>>>            Set_Attribute DF_FILE_TABLE_CHARACTER_FORMAT of hTable to sOrgFormat
92734>>>>>        Structure_End hTable (DF_STRUCTEND_OPT_IN_PLACE ior DF_STRUCTEND_OPT_FORCE)
92736>>>>>        
92736>>>>>        Function_Return (Err = False)
92737>>>>>    End_Function 
