92738>>>>>    // Checks if the passed Table;
92738>>>>>    // 1) Already has a Filelist entry that points to SQL and
92738>>>>>    // 2) It has an .int file. 
92738>>>>>    // If both is True it should already be connected to SQL
92738>>>>>    Function SQLUtilTableIsAttached String sDriverID Handle hTable Returns Boolean
92740>>>>>        Boolean bExists bRootName
92740>>>>>        String sRootName sDataPath
92740>>>>>        Integer iCount
92740>>>>>        
92740>>>>>        Get_Attribute DF_FILE_ROOT_NAME of hTable to sRootName
92743>>>>>        Move (sRootName contains sDriverID) to bRootName
92744>>>>>        
92744>>>>>        Get psDataPathFirstPart to sDataPath
92745>>>>>        Get vFolderExists sDataPath to bExists
92746>>>>>        If (bExists = False) Begin
92748>>>>>            // If the path doesn't exist it cannot have an .int file and we're done, although it shouldn't happen.
92748>>>>>            Function_Return False
92749>>>>>        End                      
92749>>>>>>
92749>>>>>        
92749>>>>>        Get vFolderFormat sDataPath to sDataPath         
92750>>>>>        Get _TableNameOnly sRootName to sRootName
92751>>>>>        Get vFilePathExists (sDataPath + sRootName + ".int") to bExists
92752>>>>>
92752>>>>>        Function_Return (bRootName = True and bExists = True)
92753>>>>>    End_Function       
